Defendant Gregory A Curtis in court with attorney John c Glover.  Defendant Gregory A Curtis in custody.  Antonella Aleman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:   

The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 2-1/2 years consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for one (1) year.  Defendant shall serve 1-1/2 years  on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for  the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 - Provide a DNA sample (unless previously provided).
 - Pay all applicable costs, fees, assessments and surcharges to be taken by the Department of Corrections from prison funds not to exceed 25%.  Balances remaining to be paid on Extended Supervision.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - Maintain absolute sobriety; no alcohol,  no controlled substances without a valid prescription.  
 - AODA assessment; treatment;
 - Random drug testing;
 - No association with known drug users or drug dealers and no contact with any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged or distributed.
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive behavorial therapy/criminal thinking programming if not already completed while in prison.
 - Pay any balances remaining of the court costs and surchages in regular, monthly payments until paid in full.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant or tax intercept.

